for Eurovision, it has been normal for RTBF to hold an internal selection process (although it has been known for RTBF to hold a national final at times, for example in [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 1998|1998]], [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2005|2005]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geocities.com/national_finals_90s_00s/Belgium1998.html |title=Belgian National Final 1998 |accessdate=2009-04-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091022062638/http://geocities.com/national_finals_90s_00s/Belgium1998.html |archivedate=22 October 2009 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geocities.com/national_finals_90s_00s/Belgium2005.html |title=Belgian National Final 2005 |accessdate=2009-04-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091022081917/http://geocities.com/national_finals_90s_00s/Belgium2005.html |archivedate=22 October 2009 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> and [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2011|2011]], while VRT internally chose Tom Dice for the 2010 edition and Sennek for the 2018 edition).\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: left; width: 500px;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Selection process\n! Broadcaster\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1956|1956]] || Internal selection || [[RTBF|INR]] ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1957|1957]] || Artist: Internal selection<br>Song: National final with 3 songs || [[Vlaamse Radio- en Televisieomroeporganisatie|NIR]] ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1958|1958]] || National final || INR ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1959|1959]] || National final with 2 participants || NIR ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1960|1960]] || National final with 5 participants || INR ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1961|1961]] || National final with 6 participants || BRT ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1962|1962]] || National final with 5 participants || RTB ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1963|1963]] || National final with 6 participants || B