icated during the broadcast.}}\n|rowspan=\"3\" colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"99999\" {{N/A|No semi-finals}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1999}}\n|[[Vanessa Chinitor]] \n|English\n|\"[[Like the Wind]]\"\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|38\n|- bgcolor=\"#fe8080\"\n!{{Escyr|2000}}\n|[[Nathalie Sorce]] \n|French\n|\"[[Envie de vivre]]\"\n|align=center|24 \u25c1\n|align=center|2\n|-\n|{{N/A|{{Escyr|2001}}}}\n|colspan=\"7\" {{N/A|Did not participate}} \n|-\n!{{Escyr|2002}}\n|[[Sergio & The Ladies]] \n|English\n|\"[[Sister (Sergio & The Ladies song)|Sister]]\"\n|align=center|13\n|align=center|33\n|rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"99999\" {{N/A|No semi-finals}}\n|- bgcolor=\"silver\"\n!{{Escyr|2003}}\n|[[Urban Trad]] \n|[[Imaginary language|Imaginary]]\n|\"[[Sanomi]]\"\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|165\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2004}}\n|[[Xandee]] \n|English\n|\"[[1 Life]]\"\n|align=center|22\n|align=center|7\n|colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"-9999\" {{N/A|Top 11 Previous Year}}{{efn|name=note2|According to the [[Rules of the Eurovision Song Contest|then-Eurovision rules]], the top ten non-[[Eurovision Song Contest#Big Four and Big Five|Big Four]] countries from the previous year along with the Big Four automatically qualified for the Grand Final without having to compete in semi-finals. For example, if Germany and France placed inside the top ten, the 11th and 12th spots were advanced to next year's Grand Final along with all countries ranked in the top ten.}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2005}}\n|[[Nuno Resende]] \n|French\n|\"[[Le grand soir (song)|Le grand soir]]\"\n|rowspan=\"5\" colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"99999\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|22\n|align=center|29\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2006}}\n|[[Kate Ryan]] \n|English{{Efn|Although the song is in English, the French title is repeated throughout the song.}} \n|\"[[Je t'adore]]\"\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|69\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2007}}\n|[[The KMG's]] \n|English\n|\"[[Love Power (The KMG's song)|Love Power]]\"\n|align=center|26\n|align=center|14\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2008}}\n|[[Ishtar (band)|Ishtar]] \n|Imaginary\n|\"[[O Julissi]]\"\n|align=center|17\n|align=center|16\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2009}}\n|[[Patrick Ouch\u00e8ne|Copycat]]\n|English\n|\"[[Copycat (Patrick Ouch\u00e8ne song)|Copycat]]\"\n|align=center|17\n|align=center|1\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2010}}\n|[[Tom Dice]]\n|English\n|\"[[Me and My Guitar (Tom Dice song)|Me and My Guitar]]\"\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|143\n|align=center bgcolor=\"gold\"|1\n|align=center bgcolor=\"gold\"|167\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2011}}\n||[[Witloof Bay]]\n|English\n|\"[[With Love Baby]]\"\n|rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"99999\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|11\n|align=center|53\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2012}}\n|[[Iris (singer)|Iris]]\n|English\n|\"[[Would You? (Iris song)|Would You?]]\"\n|align=center|17\n|align=center|16\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2013}}\n|[[Roberto Bellarosa]]\n|English\n|\"[[Love Kills (Roberto Bellarosa song)|Love Kills]]\"\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|71\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|75\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2014}}\n|[[Axel Hirsoux]]\n|English\n|\"[[Mother (Axel Hirsoux song)|Mother]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|14\n|align=center|28\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2015}}\n|[[Lo\u00efc Nottet]]\n|English\n|\"[[Rhythm Inside (Lo\u00efc Nottet song)|Rhythm Inside]]\"\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|217\n|align=center bgcolor=\"silver\"|2\n|align=center bgcolor=\"silver\"|149\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2016}}\n|[[Laura Tesoro]] \n|English\n|\"[[What's the Pressure]]\"\n|align=center|10\n|align=center|181\n|align=center bgcolor=\"#cc9966\"|3\n|align=center bgcolor=\"#cc9966\"|274\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2017}}\n|[[Blanche (singer)|Blanche]]\n|English\n|\"[[City Lights (Blanche song)|City Lights]]\"\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|363\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|165\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2018}}\n|[[Laura Groeseneken|Sennek]]\n|English\n|\"[[A Matter of Time (Sennek song)|A Matter of Time]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|91\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2019}}\n|[[Eliot Vassamillet|Eliot]]\n|English\n|\"[[Wake Up (Eliot song)|Wake Up]]\"\n|align=center|13\n|align=center|70\n|-bgcolor=\"#A4EAA9\"\n|{{N/A|{{Escyr|2020}}}}{{Efn|The 2020 contest was cancelled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].}}\n|[[Hooverphonic]]\n| English\n|\"[[Release Me (Hooverphonic song)|Release Me]]\"\n|colspan=\"4\" {{N/A|Contest cancelled}} '''X'''\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2021}}\n|[[Hooverphonic]]\n|\n|\n|align=center|\n|align=center|\n|align=center|\n|align=center|\n|}\n\n==Selection process==\nWhile VRT normally hosts a national final, [[Eurosong (Belgium)|Eurosong]], when selecting their entries for Eurovision, it has been normal for RTBF to hold an internal selection process (although it has been known for RTBF to hold a national final at times, for example in [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 1998|1998]], [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2005|2005]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geocities.com/national_finals_90s_00s/Belgium1998.html |title=Belgian National Final 1998 |accessdate=2009-04-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091022062638/http://geocities.com/national_finals_90s_00s/Belgium1998.html |archivedate=22 October 2009 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geocities.com/national_finals_90s_00s/Belgium2005.html |title=Belgian National Final 2005 |accessdate=2009-04-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091022081917/http://geocities.com/national_finals_90s_00s/Belgium2005.html |archivedate=22 October 2009 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> and [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2011|2011]], while VRT internally chose Tom Dice for the 2010 edition and Sennek for the 2018 edition).\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: left; width: 500px;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Selection process\n! Broadcaster\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1956|1956]] || Internal selection || [[RTBF|INR]] ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1957|1957]] || Artist: Internal selection<br>Song: National final with 3 songs || [[Vlaamse Radio- en Televisieomroeporganisatie|NIR]] ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1958|1958]] || National final || INR ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1959|1959]] || National final with 2 participants || NIR ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1960|1960]] || National final with 5 participants || INR ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1961|1961]] || National final with 6 participants || BRT ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1962|1962]] || National final with 5 participants || RTB ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1963|1963]] || National final with 6 participants || BRT ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1964|1964]] || Internal selection || RTB ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1965|1965]] || Artist: Internal selection<br>Song: National final with 6 songs || BRT ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1966|1966]] || Artist: Internal selection<br>Song: National final with 4 songs || RTB ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1967|1967]] || National final with 7 participants || BRT ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1968|1968]] || National final with 10 participants || RTB ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1969|1969]] || Artist: Internal selection<br>Song: National final with 6 songs || BRT ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1970|1970]] || National final with 4 participants || RTB ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1971|1971]] || National final with 12 participants || BRT ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1972|1972]] || Artist: Internal selection<br>Song: National final with 10 songs || RTB ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1973|1973]] || National final with 10 participants || BRT ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1974|1974]] || Artist: Internal selection<br>Song: National final with 6 songs || RTB ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1975|1975]] || National final with 10 participants || BRT ||\n|-\n| [[Eurovision Song Contest 1976|1976]] || National final with 5 participants || RTB ||\n|-\n| [[