an Women's Volleyball Championship|1979 Hong Kong]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[1987 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|1987 Shanghai]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[1989 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|1989 Hong Kong]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[1991 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|1991 Bangkok]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[1993 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|1993 Shanghai]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[1995 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|1995 Chiang Mai]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[1997 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|1997 Manila]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[1999 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|1999 Hong Kong]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2001 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|2001 Nakhon Ratchasima]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2003 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|2003 Ho Chi Minh City]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2005 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|2005 Taicang]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2011 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|2011 Taipei]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2015 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|2015 Tianjin]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[1983 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|1983 Fukuoka]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2007 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|2007 Nakhon Ratchasima]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2009 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|2009 Hanoi]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[1975 Asian Women's Volleyball Championship|1975 Melbourne]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[AVC Cup for Women|Asian Cup]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2008 Asian Women's Volleyball Cup|2008 Nakhon Ratchasima]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2010 Asian Women's Volleyball Cup|2010 Taicang]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2014 Asian Women's Volleyball Cup|2014 Shenzhen]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2016 Asian Women's Volleyball Cup|2016 V\u0129nh Ph\u00fac]]|}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2018 Asian Women's Volleyball Cup|2018 Nakhon Ratchasima]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2012 Asian Women's Volleyball Cup|2012 Almaty]]|}}\n}}\nThe '''China women's national volleyball team''' ({{zh|s=\u4e2d\u56fd\u56fd\u5bb6\u5973\u5b50\u6392\u7403\u961f, or \u4e2d\u56fd\u5973\u6392 for short}}) represents the [[People's Republic of China]] in international [[volleyball]] competitions and friendly matches, governed by [[Chinese Volleyball Association]]. They are one of the leading and most successful squads in women's international volleyball, having won ten championships titles in the three major international competitions of volleyball, including five [[FIVB Volleyball Women's World Cup|World Cups]] (1981, 1985, 2003, 2015, 2019), two [[FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship|World Championships]] (1982, 1986) and three [[Volleyball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic titles]] (1984, 2004, 2016). The current head coach is [[Lang Ping]].\n\nChina took five consecutive World titles in the 1980s. Although it experienced an unstable development in the 1990s, the team won the World Cup title in 2003, 2015 and 2019, also captured the gold medal in the [[Volleyball at the 2004 Summer Olympics|2004 Summer Olympics]] and [[Volleyball at the 2016 Summer Olympics|2016 Summer Olympics]].  In 2011, 2014, 2015 and 2016, the Chinese women's volleyball team won the \"Best team\" award in the CCTV sportsmanship competition.\n\n== Achievements ==\nUpdated after [[2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Cup|2019 Women's World Cup]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=30% style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Competition !!{{GoldMedal}} !!{{SilverMedal}} !!{{BronzeMedal}} !!Total\n|-\n|align=left|[[Volleyball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]\n| 3 || 1 || 2 || 6\n|-\n|align=left|[[FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship|World Championship]]\n| 2 || 3 || 1 || 6\n|-\n|align=left|[[FIVB Volleyball Women's World Cup|World Cup]]\n| 5 || 1 || 3 || 9\n|-\n|align=left|[[FIVB Volleyball World Grand Champions Cup|World Grand Champions Cup]]\n| 2 || 1 || 1 || 4\n|-\n|align=left|[[FIVB Volleyball World Grand Prix|World Grand Prix]]\n| 1 || 5 || 3 || 9\n|-\n|align=left|[[FIVB Volleyball Women's Nations League|Volleyball Nations League]]\n| 0 || 0 || 2 || 2\n|-\n|align=left|[[Volleyball at the Asian Games|Asian Games