 yellow\n|list1=\n{{China Squad 1982 FIVB Women's World Championship}}\n{{China Squad 1986 FIVB Women's World Championship}}\n{{China Squad 1990 FIVB Women's World Championship}}\n{{China Squad 1998 FIVB Women's World Championship}}\n{{China Squad 2014 FIVB Women's World Championship}}\n{{China Squad 2018 FIVB Women's World Championship}}\n}}\n\n{{navboxes colour\n|title=World Cup squads\n|bg= red\n|fg= yellow\n|list1=\n{{China Squad 1981 FIVB Women's World Cup}}\n{{China Squad 1985 FIVB Women's World Cup}}\n{{China Squad 1989 FIVB Women's World Cup}}\n{{China Squad 1991 FIVB Women's World Cup}}\n{{China Squad 1995 FIVB Women's World Cup}}\n{{China Squad 2003 FIVB Women's World Cup}}\n{{China Squad 2011 FIVB Women's World Cup}}\n{{China squad 2015 FIVB Women's World Cup}}\n{{China squad 2019 FIVB Women's World Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{navboxes colour\n|title=Olympic Games squads\n|bg= red\n|fg= yellow\n|list1=\n{{China women volleyball team 1984 Olympics}}\n{{China women volleyball team 1988 Olympics}}\n{{China women volleyball team 1996 Olympics}}\n{{China women volleyball team 2004 Olympics}}\n{{China women volleyball team 2008 Olympics}}\n{{China women's volleyball squad 2016 Summer Olympics}}\n}}\n\n== In Popular Culture ==\n[[Leap (film)|Leap (2020)]] was a film based on the China Women's national volleyball team directed by [[Peter Chan]] and starring [[Gong Li]] as [[Lang Ping]]. Actual members of the team's Rio Olympic squad, including current team captain [[Zhu Ting (volleyball)|Zhu Ting]], former team captain [[Hui Ruoqi]], setter [[Ding Xia]], middle blockers [[Xu Yunli]], [[Yan Ni (volleyball)|Yan Ni]], [[Yuan Xinyue]], outside hitters [[Zhang Changning]], [[Liu Xiaotong|Liu XIao Tong,]] opposite spiker [[Gong Xiangyu]] and libero [[Lin Li (volleyball)|Lin Li]], were cast to play themselves in the film. The current national team setter [[Yao Di (volleyball)|Yao Di]] was cast to play setter [[Wei Qiuyue]], who was pregnant at the time of filming. \n\n==See also==\n