{"title_page": "Nth room case", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=March 2020}}\n{{grammar|date=April 2020}}\n'''Nth room case'''<ref>{{cite news |date= 25 March 2020|title= \nTelegram sex offender's case sent to prosecution|url= http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200325000174 |work= The Korea Herald |location=Seoul |access-date= 25 March 2020|agency=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref> ({{Korean|n\ubc88\ubc29 \uc0ac\uac74|n\u756a\u623f \u4e8b\u4ef6}}) is a digital sexual crime case that occurred on the application [[Telegram (software)|Telegram]] from 2018 to 2020 in [[South Korea]].<ref name=\"n\">{{cite press release|last= |first= |date= 20 March 2020|title= \uc131\ucc29\ucde8\ubb3c \uc81c\uc791\u2027\uc720\ud3ec \ud154\ub808\uadf8\ub7a8 \uff62\ubc15\uc0ac\ubc29\uff63 \uc6b4\uc601\uc790 \uac80\uac70|url= https://www.smpa.go.kr/user/nd42986.do?View&boardNo=00236016 |publisher=Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency |location=Seoul |access-date= 24 March 2020|lang=Korean}}</ref> This case is generally described as the Nth room case, with the name referring to the activity of several individuals.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://imnews.imbc.com/replay/2020/nwdesk/article/5674586_32524.html|title=Distributing pornography by telegram ... 'Dr. Bang' was caught|author=SHIN Sua (\uc2e0\uc218\uc544) |date=Mar 20, 2020|work=MBC News|access-date=|url-status=live|language=Korean|}}</ref> The most well known case involves the '''Nth room''', operated by a man using the name '''God God''' (Korean: \uac13\uac13) who sold sexual exploitation videos in Telegram chatrooms named from the \"1st room\" up to the \"8th room\". Similarly, there was a '''Doctor's room''' ({{Korean|\ubc15\uc0ac\ubc29|\u535a\u58eb\u623f|baksabang}}) operated by a man using the screen name '''Doctor''' ({{Korean|\ubc15\uc0ac|\u535a\u58eb|Baksa}}, later revealed to be '''[[Cho Joo-bin]]''',<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|title=Face of notorious child porn suspect revealed|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2020/03/251_286686.html|journal=The Korea Times|volume=|pages=|via=|date=March 24, 2020|agency=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref>), who blackmailed dozens of women, forcing them to take sexually exploitative videos.<ref name=\"bbc20200325\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-52030219|date=25 March 2020|title=Cho Ju-bin: South Korea chatroom sex abuse suspect named after outcry|author=Laura Bicker|newspaper=BBC News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/south-korea-identifies-suspected-leader-of-sexual-blackmail-ring-after-uproar/2020/03/25/f45f9df4-6e5f-11ea-a156-0048b62cdb51_story.html|title=South Korea identifies suspected leader of sexual blackmail ring after uproar|newspaper=The Washington Post|author=Min Joo Kim|date=March 25, 2020|location=Seoul}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/25/outrage-in-south-korea-over-telegram-sexual-abuse-ring-blackmailing-women-and-girls|title=Outrage in South Korea over Telegram sexual abuse ring blackmailing women and girls|author=Justin McCurry|location=Tokyo|date=Mar 25, 2020|newspaper=Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/25/world/asia/south-korea-pornography-online.html|title=Suspect Held in South Korean Crackdown on Sexually Explicit Videos|author=Choe Sang-Hun|location=SEOUL, South Korea|date=March 25, 2020|newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\nThere were at least 10,000 members of the \"sample room\" of \"Doctor's room\".{{citation needed span|date=March 2020|It is estimated that there were at least 30,000, and perhaps up to a maximum of 300,000 paid members of \"Doctor's room\".}} The number of confirmed victims is a minimum of 74, and 16 minors, including some children.{{citation needed span|date=March 2020|and there are claims that there are a few thousand up to a few ten thousand victims.}}\n\n== Case ==\nIn February 2019, the fact that there was a Telegram chatroom where the perpetrators called the victims \"slaves\" and uploaded pictures of sexual exploitation, even sharing personal information, became known. It became known on popular South Korean, male dominant online communities such as [[Ilbe Storehouse|Ilbe Storage (Ilbe)]] and the erotic gallery and study gallery of dcinside.\n\n===\"nth room\"===\nSomeone with the nickname \"God God\" created the \"1st room\" up to the \"8th room\" (nicknamed \"nth room\"), and uploaded pornography of sexual exploitation. Someone with the nickname \"watchman\" uploaded that link and allowed it to be accessed in a Telegram room called \"Gotham room\". However nth room disappeared in September 2019, and other rooms appeared instead.\n\n===\"Doctor's room\"===\nIt is true that Nth room started first, but it is more bizarre, the magnitude of the damage and the number of victims is much larger, and the place where the crime was conducted is the Doctor's room. One fact is that 16 of the officially known victims were minors, including middle school students.{{citation needed span|date=March 2020|along with the fact that there are 30,000 paid members who traded those videos.}} In Doctor's room, sexually exploitative pornography was distributed via a Telegram chatroom, and was only accessible by crypto-currency payment. \"Doctor\", who appeared in July 2019, threatened women, and took sadistic pictures and videos by figuring out their personal information, and then uploaded these pictures and videos. When reports first started, Doctor even figured out the personal information of the reporter, and circulated it. In addition, a high school student in Incheon was running various Telegram chatting rooms that distributed child pornography and links for buying drugs, and even shared tricks for dealing with police investigations.\n\n===Copycat crime===\nnth room gave birth to a Doctor's room that mimics it, and other copycat crimes are occurring.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.kbs.co.kr/news/view.do?ncd=4404749|title=N\ubc88\ubc29 \uc720\ub825 \uc6b4\uc601\uc790 \uac80\uac70\ub41c \uc640\uc911\uc5d0\ub3c4\u2026\u201c\uc81c2\u00b7\uc81c3 N\ubc88\ubc29 \uc5ec\uc804\u201d|website=KBS \ub274\uc2a4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20200324176800062|title='\uac13\uac13' \ubaa8\ubc29 '\uc81c2n\ubc88\ubc29' \uc6b4\uc601\uc790 \ub610 \uc788\ub2e4\u2026\ub2c9\ub124\uc784 '\ub85c\ub9ac\ub300\uc7a5\ud0dc\ubc94'|last=\uc774\uc7ac\ud604|date=2020-03-24|website=\uc5f0\ud569\ub274\uc2a4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n==Reports and investigation==\nIn the beginning, when the case became known on male-dominated online communities, Jaesoo Kim (fictitious name) reported the nth room case by contacting 112 (number for police). However, police did not view it as a credible report, and ignored it.\n\nIn January 2019, the ''[[Seoul Shinmun]]'' found out by conducting undercover journalism that there was a secret Telegram room that was distributing child pornography, and to this point has not revealed the substance of the case. In the same manner, in April 2019, ''Sisa Journal'' reported that Telegram was being used as a platform for crime, in sharing illegal pictures and videos. On August 12, the ''Electronic Times'' was the first press outlet to report nth room. Thus, this case has brought huge social impact and public fury.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20200323002900315|title=Sex crime chat room ignites public fury|date=Mar 23, 2020|work=|access-date=|url-status=live|agency=Yonhap News Agency|location=Seoul}}</ref>\n\nRepresentative operator Baksa was arrested and released,<ref name=\"bbc20200325\"/> but his accomplice and Telegram users who share these videos trade for money are still unknown. Over 2 million have signed a national petition requesting the South Korean government to disclose the identity of users who have shared in the chatroom.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www1.president.go.kr/petitions/586819|title=\ud154\ub808\uadf8\ub7a8 n\ubc88\ubc29 \uc6a9\uc758\uc790 \uc2e0\uc0c1\uacf5\uac1c \ubc0f \ud3ec\ud1a0\ub77c\uc778 \uc138\uc6cc\uc8fc\uc138\uc694|last=|first=|date=Mar 18, 2020|website=[[Petitions to Blue House]]|publisher=The official website of the Republic of Korea \u00b7 Office of the President (Cheong Wa Dae) |url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|lang=Korean}}</ref>\n\nOn March 25, 2020 Korean virtual and crypto-currency operators agreed to cooperate with authorities in connection with this case, by determining that the leaders and subscribers of nth room paid with virtual currency.\n\n== Suspects ==\nOn March 23, 2020, [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] first disclosed the identity of the \"Doctor's room\" suspect.<ref name=\"cho\">{{cite news |last= |first= |date= 23 March 2020|title= [\ub2e8\ub3c5] '\ubc15\uc0ac\ubc29' \uc6b4\uc601\uc790 \uc2e0\uc0c1 \uacf5\uac1c\u202625\uc0b4 \uc870\uc8fc\ube48|url=https://news.sbs.co.kr/news/endPage.do?news_id=N1005712335|work=SBS News |location= |author= KIM Sangmin (\uae40\uc0c1\ubbfc) |access-date= 24 March 2020|language=Korean}}</ref> His name is Cho Joo-bin (Korean: \uc870\uc8fc\ube48, born October 14, 1995).<ref name=\"cho\"/> On March 24, following a decision of the Personal Information Disclosure Review Committee of the Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency, an official identity disclosure measure was taken, on the basis of Article 25 of the Act on Special Cases Concerning the Punishment of Sexual Crimes. The suspect is Cho Joo-bin, born in 1995; this is the first case where an official identity disclosure measure has been taken for a sexual criminal. It has been revealed that Cho Joo-bin graduated from a technical college in Incheon, and was a reporter for the university newspaper. It is also suspected that he was active as a ilbe member, although this has not been confirmed.\n\nMeanwhile, the user with the nickname \"watchman\" who was known as the mastermind and the individual who made nth room popular was arrested in September 2019.  He was revealed as Mr. Jeon, a 38 year-old company worker, who had received a suspended sentence for pornography distribution in the past. Mr. Jeon was indicted on suspicion of operating an Internet site featuring illegal recordings, and a sentence of imprisonment of 3 years 6 months was sought by the prosecution. However, since it was revealed during the trial that there is a connection with nth room, an application is underway for resumption of hearings.\n\nMr. Shin, the prior operator of nth room, who had inherited it from \"God God\" was a male in his 30s, who had previously received a suspended sentence for violating the Act on the Protection of Children and Youth Against Sex Offenses, and was taken into police custody in September 2019. He received a sentence of one year imprisonment in the first hearing, and since the prosecution did not appeal, it is anticipated that this sentence will become final in the second hearing.\n\n== Reactions ==\n{{prose|section|date=March 2020}}\n\n=== Politics ===\n[[Lee In-young]], the parliamentary leader of the ruling [[Democratic Party of Korea]], promised the party will bring the case to parliament.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date= 11 February 2020|title= \ubbfc\uc8fc\ub2f9 \"\ud154\ub808\uadf8\ub7a8 N\ubc88\ubc29 \uc0ac\uac74 \uc785\ubc95, \uad6d\ubbfc\uaed8 \uc57d\uc18d\"|url= https://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1YYVR5RBQD|work=Seoul Economic Daily  |location= |access-date= 24 March 2020|author=HA Ellena (\ud558\uc815\uc5f0)|lang=Korean}}</ref>\nThe main opposition [[United Future Party]] condemned the case, in which they will forward the case to parliament to prohibits any kind of child pornography.<ref name=\"ufp\">{{cite news |last= |first= |date= 20 March 2020|title= [\ud3ec\ud1a0] \u201c\uc131\ucc29\ucde8 N\ubc88\ubc29 \ucc98\ubc8c \ubbf8\ub798\ud1b5\ud569\ub2f9\uc774 \uc55e\uc7a5\u201d|url= http://www.womennews.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=197364|work=The Women's News |location= |access-date= 24 March 2020|author=HONG Suhyeong (\ud64d\uc218\ud615)|lang=Korean}}</ref> The party also urged the Democratic Party to not just focus on the [[2020 South Korean legislative election|upcoming general election]] but also cooperate with them to forward their bill.<ref name=\"ufp\"/> Its chairman, [[Hwang Kyo-ahn]], however, created controversy by saying not all suspects involved in the case deserved the same punishment.\n\n== Expert opinion ==\nFor preventing recurrence and resolving this case, experts{{who|date=March 2020}} have indicated that the following is necessary. First, request the active international cooperation of governments. Second, establish a dedicated department for digital sexual crimes. Third, build a strong system for strengthening the weighing of offenses, and confiscating the proceeds of crime. Fourth, permitting sting investigations. Fifth, punishing the platforms. Opinions were presented that it is necessary to introduce new concepts and crime names of \"digital group sexual violence\" and \"sexual exploitation\".{{Citation needed|reason=This claim needs a reliable source. Expert opinion requires demonstration of expertise to validate opinion.|date=March 2020}}\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of sexual abuses perpetrated by groups]]\n*[[Child grooming]]\n*[[Intimidation]]\n*[[Telegram (software)]]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Sex crimes in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Telegram (software)]]\n[[Category:Cybercrime in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Child sexual abuse in South Korea]]\n[[Category:2018 in South Korea]]\n[[Category:2019 in South Korea]]\n[[Category:2020 in South Korea]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=March 2020}}\n{{grammar|date=April 2020}}\n'''Nth room case'''<ref>{{cite news |date= 25 March 2020|title= \nTelegram sex offender's case sent to prosecution|url= http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200325000174 |work= The Korea Herald |location=Seoul |access-date= 25 March 2020|agency=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref> ({{Korean|n\ubc88\ubc29 \uc0ac\uac74|n\u756a\u623f \u4e8b\u4ef6}}) is a digital sexual crime case that occurred on the application [[Telegram (software)|Telegram]] from 2018 to 2020 in [[South Korea]].<ref name=\"n\">{{cite press release|last= |first= |date= 20 March 2020|title= \uc131\ucc29\ucde8\ubb3c \uc81c\uc791\u2027\uc720\ud3ec \ud154\ub808\uadf8\ub7a8 \uff62\ubc15\uc0ac\ubc29\uff63 \uc6b4\uc601\uc790 \uac80\uac70|url= https://www.smpa.go.kr/user/nd42986.do?View&boardNo=00236016 |publisher=Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency |location=Seoul |access-date= 24 March 2020|lang=Korean}}</ref> This case is generally described as the Nth room case, with the name referring to the activity of several individuals.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://imnews.imbc.com/replay/2020/nwdesk/article/5674586_32524.html|title=Distributing pornography by telegram ... 'Dr. Bang' was caught|author=SHIN Sua (\uc2e0\uc218\uc544) |date=Mar 20, 2020|work=MBC News|access-date=|url-status=live|language=Korean|}}</ref> The most well known case involves the '''Nth room''', operated by a man using the name '''God God''' (Korean: \uac13\uac13) who sold sexual exploitation videos in Telegram chatrooms named from the \"1st room\" up to the \"8th room\". Similarly, there was a '''Doctor's room''' ({{Korean|\ubc15\uc0ac\ubc29|\u535a\u58eb\u623f|baksabang}}) operated by a man using the screen name '''Doctor''' ({{Korean|\ubc15\uc0ac|\u535a\u58eb|Baksa}}, later revealed to be '''[[Cho Joo-bin]]''',<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|title=Face of notorious child porn suspect revealed|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2020/03/251_286686.html|journal=The Korea Times|volume=|pages=|via=|date=March 24, 2020|agency=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref>) who blackmailed dozens of women, forcing them to take sexually exploitative videos.<ref name=\"bbc20200325\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-52030219|date=25 March 2020|title=Cho Ju-bin: South Korea chatroom sex abuse suspect named after outcry|author=Laura Bicker|newspaper=BBC News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/south-korea-identifies-suspected-leader-of-sexual-blackmail-ring-after-uproar/2020/03/25/f45f9df4-6e5f-11ea-a156-0048b62cdb51_story.html|title=South Korea identifies suspected leader of sexual blackmail ring after uproar|newspaper=The Washington Post|author=Min Joo Kim|date=March 25, 2020|location=Seoul}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/25/outrage-in-south-korea-over-telegram-sexual-abuse-ring-blackmailing-women-and-girls|title=Outrage in South Korea over Telegram sexual abuse ring blackmailing women and girls|author=Justin McCurry|location=Tokyo|date=Mar 25, 2020|newspaper=Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/25/world/asia/south-korea-pornography-online.html|title=Suspect Held in South Korean Crackdown on Sexually Explicit Videos|author=Choe Sang-Hun|location=SEOUL, South Korea|date=March 25, 2020|newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\nThere were at least 10,000 members of the \"sample room\" of \"Doctor's room\".{{citation needed span|date=March 2020|It is estimated that there were at least 30,000, and perhaps up to a maximum of 300,000 paid members of \"Doctor's room\".}} The number of confirmed victims is a minimum of 74, and 16 minors, including some children.{{citation needed span|date=March 2020|and there are claims that there are a few thousand up to a few ten thousand victims.}}\n\n== Case ==\nIn February 2019, the fact that there was a Telegram chatroom where the perpetrators called the victims \"slaves\" and uploaded pictures of sexual exploitation, even sharing personal information, became known. It became known on popular South Korean, male dominant online communities such as [[Ilbe Storehouse|Ilbe Storage (Ilbe)]] and the erotic gallery and study gallery of dcinside.\n\n===\"nth room\"===\nSomeone with the nickname \"God God\" created the \"1st room\" up to the \"8th room\" (nicknamed \"nth room\"), and uploaded pornography of sexual exploitation. Someone with the nickname \"watchman\" uploaded that link and allowed it to be accessed in a Telegram room called \"Gotham room\". However nth room disappeared in September 2019, and other rooms appeared instead.\n\n===\"Doctor's room\"===\nIt is true that Nth room started first, but it is more bizarre, the magnitude of the damage and the number of victims is much larger, and the place where the crime was conducted is the Doctor's room. One fact is that 16 of the officially known victims were minors, including middle school students.{{citation needed span|date=March 2020|along with the fact that there are 30,000 paid members who traded those videos.}} In Doctor's room, sexually exploitative pornography was distributed via a Telegram chatroom, and was only accessible by crypto-currency payment. \"Doctor\", who appeared in July 2019, threatened women, and took sadistic pictures and videos by figuring out their personal information, and then uploaded these pictures and videos. When reports first started, Doctor even figured out the personal information of the reporter, and circulated it. In addition, a high school student in Incheon was running various Telegram chatting rooms that distributed child pornography and links for buying drugs, and even shared tricks for dealing with police investigations.\n\n===Copycat crime===\nnth room gave birth to a Doctor's room that mimics it, and other copycat crimes are occurring.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.kbs.co.kr/news/view.do?ncd=4404749|title=N\ubc88\ubc29 \uc720\ub825 \uc6b4\uc601\uc790 \uac80\uac70\ub41c \uc640\uc911\uc5d0\ub3c4\u2026\u201c\uc81c2\u00b7\uc81c3 N\ubc88\ubc29 \uc5ec\uc804\u201d|website=KBS \ub274\uc2a4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20200324176800062|title='\uac13\uac13' \ubaa8\ubc29 '\uc81c2n\ubc88\ubc29' \uc6b4\uc601\uc790 \ub610 \uc788\ub2e4\u2026\ub2c9\ub124\uc784 '\ub85c\ub9ac\ub300\uc7a5\ud0dc\ubc94'|last=\uc774\uc7ac\ud604|date=2020-03-24|website=\uc5f0\ud569\ub274\uc2a4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n==Reports and investigation==\nIn the beginning, when the case became known on male-dominated online communities, Jaesoo Kim (fictitious name) reported the nth room case by contacting 112 (number for police). However, police did not view it as a credible report, and ignored it.\n\nIn January 2019, the ''[[Seoul Shinmun]]'' found out by conducting undercover journalism that there was a secret Telegram room that was distributing child pornography, and to this point has not revealed the substance of the case. In the same manner, in April 2019, ''Sisa Journal'' reported that Telegram was being used as a platform for crime, in sharing illegal pictures and videos. On August 12, the ''Electronic Times'' was the first press outlet to report nth room. Thus, this case has brought huge social impact and public fury.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20200323002900315|title=Sex crime chat room ignites public fury|date=Mar 23, 2020|work=|access-date=|url-status=live|agency=Yonhap News Agency|location=Seoul}}</ref>\n\nRepresentative operator Baksa was arrested and released,<ref name=\"bbc20200325\"/> but his accomplice and Telegram users who share these videos trade for money are still unknown. Over 2 million have signed a national petition requesting the South Korean government to disclose the identity of users who have shared in the chatroom.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www1.president.go.kr/petitions/586819|title=\ud154\ub808\uadf8\ub7a8 n\ubc88\ubc29 \uc6a9\uc758\uc790 \uc2e0\uc0c1\uacf5\uac1c \ubc0f \ud3ec\ud1a0\ub77c\uc778 \uc138\uc6cc\uc8fc\uc138\uc694|last=|first=|date=Mar 18, 2020|website=[[Petitions to Blue House]]|publisher=The official website of the Republic of Korea \u00b7 Office of the President (Cheong Wa Dae) |url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|lang=Korean}}</ref>\n\nOn March 25, 2020 Korean virtual and crypto-currency operators agreed to cooperate with authorities in connection with this case, by determining that the leaders and subscribers of nth room paid with virtual currency.\n\n== Suspects ==\nOn March 23, 2020, [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] first disclosed the identity of the \"Doctor's room\" suspect.<ref name=\"cho\">{{cite news |last= |first= |date= 23 March 2020|title= [\ub2e8\ub3c5] '\ubc15\uc0ac\ubc29' \uc6b4\uc601\uc790 \uc2e0\uc0c1 \uacf5\uac1c\u202625\uc0b4 \uc870\uc8fc\ube48|url=https://news.sbs.co.kr/news/endPage.do?news_id=N1005712335|work=SBS News |location= |author= KIM Sangmin (\uae40\uc0c1\ubbfc) |access-date= 24 March 2020|language=Korean}}</ref> His name is Cho Joo-bin (Korean: \uc870\uc8fc\ube48, born October 14, 1995).<ref name=\"cho\"/> On March 24, following a decision of the Personal Information Disclosure Review Committee of the Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency, an official identity disclosure measure was taken, on the basis of Article 25 of the Act on Special Cases Concerning the Punishment of Sexual Crimes. The suspect is Cho Joo-bin, born in 1995; this is the first case where an official identity disclosure measure has been taken for a sexual criminal. It has been revealed that Cho Joo-bin graduated from a technical college in Incheon, and was a reporter for the university newspaper. It is also suspected that he was active as a ilbe member, although this has not been confirmed.\n\nMeanwhile, the user with the nickname \"watchman\" who was known as the mastermind and the individual who made nth room popular was arrested in September 2019.  He was revealed as Mr. Jeon, a 38 year-old company worker, who had received a suspended sentence for pornography distribution in the past. Mr. Jeon was indicted on suspicion of operating an Internet site featuring illegal recordings, and a sentence of imprisonment of 3 years 6 months was sought by the prosecution. However, since it was revealed during the trial that there is a connection with nth room, an application is underway for resumption of hearings.\n\nMr. Shin, the prior operator of nth room, who had inherited it from \"God God\" was a male in his 30s, who had previously received a suspended sentence for violating the Act on the Protection of Children and Youth Against Sex Offenses, and was taken into police custody in September 2019. He received a sentence of one year imprisonment in the first hearing, and since the prosecution did not appeal, it is anticipated that this sentence will become final in the second hearing.\n\n== Reactions ==\n{{prose|section|date=March 2020}}\n\n=== Politics ===\n[[Lee In-young]], the parliamentary leader of the ruling [[Democratic Party of Korea]], promised the party will bring the case to parliament.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date= 11 February 2020|title= \ubbfc\uc8fc\ub2f9 \"\ud154\ub808\uadf8\ub7a8 N\ubc88\ubc29 \uc0ac\uac74 \uc785\ubc95, \uad6d\ubbfc\uaed8 \uc57d\uc18d\"|url= https://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1YYVR5RBQD|work=Seoul Economic Daily  |location= |access-date= 24 March 2020|author=HA Ellena (\ud558\uc815\uc5f0)|lang=Korean}}</ref>\nThe main opposition [[United Future Party]] condemned the case, in which they will forward the case to parliament to prohibits any kind of child pornography.<ref name=\"ufp\">{{cite news |last= |first= |date= 20 March 2020|title= [\ud3ec\ud1a0] \u201c\uc131\ucc29\ucde8 N\ubc88\ubc29 \ucc98\ubc8c \ubbf8\ub798\ud1b5\ud569\ub2f9\uc774 \uc55e\uc7a5\u201d|url= http://www.womennews.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=197364|work=The Women's News |location= |access-date= 24 March 2020|author=HONG Suhyeong (\ud64d\uc218\ud615)|lang=Korean}}</ref> The party also urged the Democratic Party to not just focus on the [[2020 South Korean legislative election|upcoming general election]] but also cooperate with them to forward their bill.<ref name=\"ufp\"/> Its chairman, [[Hwang Kyo-ahn]], however, created controversy by saying not all suspects involved in the case deserved the same punishment.\n\n== Expert opinion ==\nFor preventing recurrence and resolving this case, experts{{who|date=March 2020}} have indicated that the following is necessary. First, request the active international cooperation of governments. Second, establish a dedicated department for digital sexual crimes. Third, build a strong system for strengthening the weighing of offenses, and confiscating the proceeds of crime. Fourth, permitting sting investigations. Fifth, punishing the platforms. Opinions were presented that it is necessary to introduce new concepts and crime names of \"digital group sexual violence\" and \"sexual exploitation\".{{Citation needed|reason=This claim needs a reliable source. Expert opinion requires demonstration of expertise to validate opinion.|date=March 2020}}\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of sexual abuses perpetrated by groups]]\n*[[Child grooming]]\n*[[Intimidation]]\n*[[Telegram (software)]]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Sex crimes in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Telegram (software)]]\n[[Category:Cybercrime in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Child sexual abuse in South Korea]]\n[[Category:2018 in South Korea]]\n[[Category:2019 in South Korea]]\n[[Category:2020 in South Korea]]\n", "name_user": "MichaelEspersen", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nth_room_case"}
